{
  "texts": [
    "The Random Forest Model was used to analyze 63 quantitative COVID-19 characteristics from chest CT images, achieving an AUC score of 91% and an accuracy of 87.5%.",
    "The Time-Dependent SIR Model was developed to dynamically adjust control strategies by epidemic protocols, while DarkCOVIDNet proposed a method for automatic identification of COVID-19 using raw chest X-ray images, achieving high diagnostic accuracy [100, 108-110].",
    "Support Vector Regression (SVR) and Stacking-Ensemble Models were used for COVID-19 forecasting, with SVR performing the best in terms of forecasting accuracy.",
    "Coronet, pre-trained on the ImageNet dataset, achieved an overall accuracy of 89.6%, 93% accuracy and 98.2% recall for COVID-19 patients in a 4-class Fig. 33Fig.",
    "3 Schematic representation of the process of model creation with AI algorithms which depicts the data collection & transformation, model building, training & testing of model along with evaluation and deployment Fig. 5 a5Fig."
  ]
